clinical_study.brief_title: Safety and Immunogenicity of a Group B Streptococcus Vaccine in Non Pregnant and Pregnant Women 18-40 Years of Age
clinical_study.official_title: A Phase Ib/II Randomized, Observer-Blind, Controlled, Single Centre Study of a Trivalent Group B Streptococcus Vaccine in Healthy Non-Pregnant Women Leading Into a Dose-Ranging Study in Pregnant Women in South Africa

brief_summary.textblock: This study will evaluate the safety and immunogenicity of a Group B Streptococcus vaccine at one dose in healthy non pregnant women and then in three different doses in healthy pregnant women.

study_design_info.masking: Quadruple (Participant, Care Provider, Investigator, Outcomes Assessor)

primary_outcome.measure: The Percentages of Non-pregnant Subjects With Antibody Concentrations Above a Defined Threshold at One Month After the Second Vaccination.
primary_outcome.time_frame: Day 61, one month after the second vaccination
primary_outcome.description: The percentages of non-pregnant subjects with antibody concentrations above a defined threshold per serotype after the administration of two vaccine doses administered one month apart. Defined thresholds for antibody concentrations, which exceed pre-defined serotype specific ELISA values are 1, 2, 3, 5 and 8 μg/mL.

primary_outcome.measure: Antibody Geometric Mean Concentrations (GMC) in Non-pregnant Women at One Month After the Second Vaccination.
primary_outcome.time_frame: Day 61, one month after the second vaccination
primary_outcome.description: Antibody GMC per serotype in non-pregnant women after receiving two doses of the study vaccine administered one month apart .

primary_outcome.measure: The Percentages of Maternal Subjects With Antibody Concentrations Above a Defined Threshold at Day of Delivery.
primary_outcome.description: The percentages of maternal subjects with antibody concentrations above a defined threshold per serotype following the administration of one of three different doses of the study vaccine or placebo.Antibody concentrations which exceed pre-defined serotype specific ELISA values are 1, 2, 3, 5 and 8 μg/mL.

primary_outcome.measure: Antibody GMC in Maternal Subjects at Day of Delivery
primary_outcome.description: Antibody GMC per serotype in maternal subjects at day of delivery following one administration of one of three different doses of the study vaccine or placebo are reported.

secondary_outcome.measure: The Percentages of Maternal Subjects With Antibody Concentrations Above a Defined Threshold Per Serotype at One Month After Vaccination.
secondary_outcome.description: The percentages of maternal subjects with antibody concentrations above a defined threshold per serotype at one month after the administration of one of three different doses of the study vaccine or placebo. Antibody concentrations which exceed pre-defined serotype specific ELISA values are 1, 2, 3, 5 and 8 μg/mL.

secondary_outcome.measure: Antibody GMC Per Serotype in Maternal Subjects at One Month After Vaccination
secondary_outcome.description: Antibody GMC per serotype in maternal subjects at one month after the administration of one of three different doses of the study vaccine or placebo.

secondary_outcome.measure: The Percentage of Non-pregnant Subjects With Antibody Concentrations Above a Defined Threshold at One Year After the First Vaccination.
secondary_outcome.time_frame: Day 361, one year after the first vaccination
secondary_outcome.description: The percentage of non-pregnant subjects with antibody concentrations above a defined threshold per serotype after the administration of two vaccine doses one month apart. Antibody concentrations which exceed pre-defined serotype specific ELISA values are 1, 2, 3, 5 and 8 mcg/mL.

secondary_outcome.measure: Antibody GMC in Non-pregnant Subjects at One Year After the First Vaccination
secondary_outcome.time_frame: Day 361, one year after the first vaccination
secondary_outcome.description: Antibody GMC per serotype in non-pregnant subjects after receiving two doses of the study vaccine administered one month apart, at one year after first vaccination.

secondary_outcome.measure: Number of Non-pregnant Subjects Reporting Solicited and Unsolicited Adverse Events
secondary_outcome.description: Number of non-pregnant subjects reporting solicited and unsolicited adverse events following 2 injections (1 month apart) of the trivalent GBS vaccine at a dose of 20/20/20 μg with aluminum at one month after second vaccination are reported.

secondary_outcome.measure: Number of Maternal Subjects Reporting Solicited and Unsolicited Adverse Events
secondary_outcome.time_frame: From day 1 to one year after delivery
secondary_outcome.description: Number of maternal subjects reporting solicited and unsolicited adverse events following the administration of either one of three different doses of the study vaccine or placebo.

secondary_outcome.measure: Antibody GMC Per Serotype at Different Time Points in Infants
secondary_outcome.time_frame: Day 4, day 43 and day 91 after birth
secondary_outcome.description: Antibody GMC per serotype on the day of birth, at 6 weeks and 3 months of age in infants born from women who received either one of three different doses of the study vaccine or placebo.

secondary_outcome.measure: Number of Infants Reporting Serious Adverse Events
secondary_outcome.description: Number of infants born from women who received either one of three different doses of the study vaccine or placebo who reported serious adverse events

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Group 1 (Non Pregnant Women): Healthy females 18-40 years of age inclusive.
- Group 2 (Healthy Pregnant Women): Healthy pregnant women 18-40 yrs of age (between 28-35 weeks gestation)
Exclusion Criteria:
- Group 1 (Non Pregnant Women): Pregnant or nursing; History of severe allergy to previous vaccines; Known HIV positive
- Group 2 (Healthy Pregnant Women): History of severe allergy to previous vaccines; Known HIV positive
